JOHANNESBURG - A video released by an al-Qaeda linked group in Mali, suggests South African Stephen McGown and five other hostages are alive.McGown was abducted in November 2011 in Timbuktu, together with recently-released Swedish national, Johann Gustaffsson. READ: McGown's father wants Mali's help to release sonYolande Korkie is someone who knows what it's like to be a hostage.She was kidnapped by al-Qaida in May 2013 and released five hundred and fifty eight days later.READ: Yolande Korkie's book describes "558 Days" of captivityHer husband, Pierre, was killed in a botched rescue attempt by the US navy seals in December 2014.She spoke to eNCA's Joanne Joseph via skype.eNCA